---
import "../../styles/theme.css";
import "../../styles/landing.css";
import LandingHeader from "../../components/landing-header.astro";
import LandingFooter from "../../components/landing-footer.astro";

const canonicalURL = "https://freellms.vercel.app/alternatives/groq/";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="canonical" href={canonicalURL} />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Geist:wght@400;500;600;700;800;900&family=Geist+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <title>FreeLLM with Groq: Route past rate limits automatically</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="FreeLLM includes Groq as one of 8 providers and automatically routes away when Groq rate-limits. Stack 3 Groq keys for 3x the free RPM."
    />
    <meta property="og:title" content="FreeLLM with Groq: Route past rate limits automatically" />
    <meta
      property="og:description"
      content="FreeLLM includes Groq as one of 8 providers and automatically routes away when Groq rate-limits. Stack 3 Groq keys for 3x the free RPM."
    />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />

  </head>
  <body>
    <LandingHeader />
    <main>
      <article class="alt-page">
        <span class="page-eyebrow">rate limits</span>
        <h1>Beyond Groq alone: route past rate limits</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Groq is fast. Its free tier is capped at around 30 req/min per key. When you hit that
          cap, requests fail with a 429. FreeLLM includes Groq as one of 8 providers and
          routes elsewhere when Groq rate-limits, so you keep getting responses.
        </p>

        <h2>What FreeLLM adds on top of Groq</h2>
        <p>
          FreeLLM does not replace Groq. It wraps it along with 7 other providers and adds
          three things that make the free tier actually usable at scale.
        </p>

        <div class="feature-list">
          <div class="feature-item">
            <span class="feature-label">Multi-key rotation</span>
            <span class="feature-desc">
              Add 3 Groq API keys and FreeLLM round-robins across them. You get roughly
              90 req/min from Groq alone, without any changes to your application code.
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-item">
            <span class="feature-label">Automatic failover</span>
            <span class="feature-desc">
              When Groq returns a 429, the next request goes to Gemini, Mistral, Cerebras,
              or whichever provider has capacity. Your app sees a successful response.
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-item">
            <span class="feature-label">Circuit breakers</span>
            <span class="feature-desc">
              If Groq has an outage or sustained rate-limiting, FreeLLM sidelines it until
              it recovers. Other providers absorb traffic in the meantime.
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>By the numbers</h2>

        <div class="table-shell">
          <table class="alt-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Feature</th>
                <th class="freellm-col">FreeLLM + Groq</th>
                <th>Groq direct</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Rate limit (single key)</td>
                <td class="freellm-col">~30 req/min per key</td>
                <td>~30 req/min</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Max throughput with key stacking</td>
                <td class="freellm-col yes">~450 req/min (8 providers, 3 keys each)</td>
                <td>~90 req/min (3 keys, manual rotation)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Failover on 429</td>
                <td class="freellm-col yes">Yes, automatic</td>
                <td class="no">No</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Circuit breakers</td>
                <td class="freellm-col yes">Yes</td>
                <td class="no">No</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Providers</td>
                <td class="freellm-col yes">8 (Groq, Gemini, Mistral, Cerebras, and more)</td>
                <td>1</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Dashboard</td>
                <td class="freellm-col yes">Yes, real-time</td>
                <td class="no">No</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2>If you only need Groq</h2>
        <p>
          If you never hit rate limits and only want Llama models via Groq, using Groq directly
          is the simpler choice. There is no gateway to deploy, no extra latency from an
          intermediate service, and no configuration to maintain. Keep it simple when simple works.
        </p>

        <hr class="divider" />

        <h2>If rate limits are your problem</h2>
        <p>
          FreeLLM routes around rate limits automatically. You add your Groq keys (and keys
          for other providers), deploy in 2 minutes, and change one line of code. After that,
          a Groq 429 is invisible to your application.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Stack multiple Groq keys. FreeLLM rotates across them without any logic in your app.</li>
          <li>When Groq is saturated, Gemini, Mistral, and Cerebras take over. Same model family, similar output quality.</li>
          <li>Response caching cuts repeat requests to around 23ms. Groq never sees them.</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="divider" />

        <h2>The code change is one line</h2>
        <p>
          If you are already calling Groq directly with the OpenAI SDK, the change is a base URL swap.
          Your model names and message format stay the same.
        </p>

        <div class="code-shell">
          <div class="code-label">python — before (Groq direct)</div>
          <pre><code><span class="token-keyword">from</span> <span class="token-var">openai</span> <span class="token-keyword">import</span> <span class="token-var">OpenAI</span>

<span class="token-var">client</span> = <span class="token-var">OpenAI</span>(
    <span class="token-var">base_url</span>=<span class="token-string">"https://api.groq.com/openai/v1"</span>,
    <span class="token-var">api_key</span>=<span class="token-string">"gsk_..."</span>
)</code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="code-shell">
          <div class="code-label">python — after (FreeLLM, routes through Groq + 7 others)</div>
          <pre><code><span class="token-keyword">from</span> <span class="token-var">openai</span> <span class="token-keyword">import</span> <span class="token-var">OpenAI</span>

<span class="token-var">client</span> = <span class="token-var">OpenAI</span>(
    <span class="token-var">base_url</span>=<span class="token-string">"https://your-freellm-instance/v1"</span>,  <span class="token-comment"># only change</span>
    <span class="token-var">api_key</span>=<span class="token-string">"your-freellm-key"</span>
)</code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="cta-block">
          <p>Deploy FreeLLM in 2 minutes. Add your Groq keys and 7 other providers. Route past rate limits automatically.</p>
          <a href="/quickstart/" class="btn-primary">Deploy FreeLLM in 2 minutes</a>
          <div class="cta-links">
            <a href="https://github.com/Devansh-365/freellm" class="btn-ghost">Star on GitHub</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>
    <LandingFooter />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .alt-page {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem 8rem;
  }

  .alt-page .page-eyebrow {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0.375rem 0.875rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: hsla(158, 50%, 40%, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid hsla(158, 50%, 40%, 0.18);
    color: hsl(158, 50%, 65%);
    font-family: "Geist Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .alt-page h1 {
    font-family: "Geist", sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: #ffffff;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .alt-page .lead {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: hsl(0, 0%, 65%);
    margin: 0 0 3.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }

  .alt-page h2 {
    font-family: "Geist", sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: #ffffff;
    margin: 3rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .alt-page p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: hsl(0, 0%, 65%);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .alt-page ul {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .alt-page ul li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: hsl(0, 0%, 65%);
  }

  .table-shell {
    border-radius: 14px;
    border: 1px solid hsl(224, 12%, 22%);
    overflow: hidden;
    margin: 2rem 0 3rem;
  }

  .alt-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-family: "Geist", sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    background: hsl(224, 14%, 15%);
  }

  .alt-table th {
    padding: 0.875rem 1.25rem;
    text-align: left;
    background: hsl(224, 14%, 13%);
    color: hsl(158, 50%, 65%);
    font-family: "Geist Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    border-bottom: 1px solid hsl(224, 12%, 22%);
  }

  .alt-table td {
    padding: 0.875rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid hsla(158, 50%, 40%, 0.07);
    color: hsl(0, 0%, 75%);
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .alt-table tbody tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .alt-table tbody tr:hover { background: hsla(158, 50%, 40%, 0.03); }
  .alt-table td:first-child { color: hsl(0, 0%, 85%); font-weight: 500; }
  .alt-table .freellm-col { background: hsla(158, 50%, 40%, 0.05); }

  .yes { color: hsl(158, 50%, 60%); font-weight: 600; font-family: "Geist Mono", monospace; }
  .no { color: hsl(0, 50%, 55%); font-family: "Geist Mono", monospace; }
  .partial { color: hsl(38, 90%, 55%); font-family: "Geist Mono", monospace; }

  .code-shell {
    border-radius: 14px;
    border: 1px solid hsl(224, 12%, 22%);
    overflow: hidden;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem;
  }

  .code-label {
    padding: 0.625rem 1.25rem;
    background: hsl(224, 14%, 13%);
    border-bottom: 1px solid hsl(224, 12%, 22%);
    font-family: "Geist Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: hsl(0, 0%, 50%);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .code-shell pre {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem;
    background: hsl(224, 14%, 15%);
    font-family: "Geist Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: hsl(0, 0%, 88%);
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .code-shell code { background: transparent; border: none; padding: 0; color: inherit; font-size: inherit; }
  .token-comment { color: hsl(0, 0%, 45%); }
  .token-keyword { color: hsl(200, 80%, 65%); }
  .token-string  { color: hsl(158, 50%, 60%); }
  .token-var     { color: hsl(0, 0%, 85%); }

  .feature-list {
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .feature-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 0.75rem 1rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .feature-label {
    font-family: "Geist Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: hsl(158, 50%, 60%);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding-top: 0.125rem;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .feature-desc {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: hsl(0, 0%, 65%);
  }

  .cta-block {
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    border-radius: 16px;
    border: 1px solid hsla(158, 50%, 40%, 0.2);
    background: hsla(158, 50%, 40%, 0.04);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-block p { color: hsl(0, 0%, 65%); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

  .cta-block .btn-primary {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: hsl(158, 50%, 46%);
    color: #04140a;
    font-family: "Geist", sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 280ms cubic-bezier(0.32, 0.72, 0, 1);
  }

  .cta-block .btn-primary:hover { background: hsl(158, 50%, 50%); transform: translateY(-1px); }

  .cta-links {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .cta-links .btn-ghost {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.375rem;
    padding: 0.625rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: transparent;
    color: hsl(0, 0%, 65%);
    font-family: "Geist", sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    border: 1px solid hsl(224, 12%, 28%);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 280ms cubic-bezier(0.32, 0.72, 0, 1);
  }

  .cta-links .btn-ghost:hover { border-color: hsl(224, 12%, 40%); color: hsl(0, 0%, 85%); }

  .divider { border: none; border-top: 1px solid hsl(224, 12%, 20%); margin: 3rem 0; }
</style>
